ted States"},"narrative_blocks":[{"category":"politics","header":"He served in Georgia's legislature","body":"An honor graduate of Franklin College, McKinley studied law under Judge Joseph Henry Lumpkin and won election to the Georgia legislature from Oglethorpe County in 1835. He returned to the legislature during Reconstruction at his friends' urging.","number":1},{"category":"character","header":"They called him the legislature's Chesterfield","body":"McKinley was remembered for the courtesy of his manner and his wise, conservative counsel, earning the nickname the Chesterfield of the legislature. A devout Presbyterian elder, he was known as a man of broad sympathies.","number":2},{"category":"business","header":"He built Barrowville from brick he kilned himself","body":"A devoted experimental farmer, McKinley built his Gothic-style house Barrowville in 1858 and 1859 from brick fired in his own yard, adapting a design from Andrew Jackson Downing's pattern book. He kept detailed records of his plantation's agriculture and weather.","number":3},{"category":"military","header":"Sherman's army camped around his house","body":"During Sherman's March to the Sea, Barrowville was made the headquarters of a Federal encampment, with thousands of soldiers camped around it. The house narrowly escaped burning when the last troops marched away.","number":4}],"slug":"william-mckinley-1809"},"HD5910":{"id":"HD5910","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"gender":"female","birth":{"year":1849,"month":8,"day":29,"city":"Baldwin County","state":"Georgia","country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1876,"month":4,"day":15,"city":"Columbus","state":"Georgia","country":"United States"},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"is_easter_egg":false,"generation_from_thomas":8},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"parents":{"father_id":"X01989","mother_id":"H01842"},"n